---
description: Paw2Paw — anonymous peer messaging platform for marginalized Princeton students
alwaysApply: true
---

# Stack
- Next.js 16 with App Router (no Pages Router)
- TypeScript strict mode
- Tailwind CSS v4
- shadcn/ui for components
- Supabase (Postgres + Auth + Realtime)
- Drizzle ORM
- Vercel for deployment
- Target: responsive web platform (mobile-first, desktop-supported)

# Architecture rules
- Server Components by default; only use 'use client' when truly necessary (forms, hooks, interactivity)
- Row-Level Security policies are the source of truth for authorization, never application code
- Never log message content. PII must be hashed at the boundary.
- All user-facing copy lives in dedicated files (no inline strings in components)

# Code style
- kebab-case for files, PascalCase for components
- Functional components only
- Always add loading and error states to async UI
- Zod for runtime validation, especially at API boundaries

# Workflow
- Before writing code, propose a plan and wait for approval
- After any architectural change, update this file
- Never commit secrets — use .env.local
- Postgres: `DATABASE_URL` = Transaction pooler :6543 (app); `DATABASE_MIGRATE_URL` = Session pooler :5432 (migrate/studio; avoid Direct — IPv6-only on many projects)
- Auth: Supabase email/password; `SIGN_DISPLAY_ID_SECRET` for display ID hashing; profile via `ensureUserProfile` on signUp (if session) + signIn (always); disable Confirm email in dev, signIn still upserts for production
- Match flow: FIFO browse on `/respond` (`topic_tags &&` overlap); claim via `claim_thread_for_responder` RPC; browse RLS `threads_select_claimable` + `messages_select_on_claimable_thread`; v2 design in `docs/matching.md`
- Conversation: `/thread/[id]` realtime channel `conversation:{threadId}`; `send_message` + `close_thread` RPCs; no read receipts/typing; soft close; design notes in `docs/conversation-design.md`; enable `messages` on `supabase_realtime` publication
